<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7B164A7BBEFAA527BDFA60" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7B164A7BBEFAA527BDFA60" blockId="11.[136,1452,1382,1984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B7B164A7BBEFAA52301FA28" box="[1003,1115,1383,1409]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Lectotype</typeStatus>
(designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7B164A7D47FAA427EEFA0C" author="Fryxell, P. A." pageId="11" pageNumber="116" pagination="589 - 593" refId="ref18668" refString="Fryxell, P. A. (1976) On some Brazilian Malvaceae of Martius, published by Colla in 1833. Taxon 25: 589 - 593. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1220115" type="journal article" year="1976">Fryxell 1976: 591</bibRefCitation>
, as “ 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B7B164A78BFFA48260CFA0C" box="[234,342,1418,1445]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">holotype</typeStatus>
”): 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7B164A7921FA4826E6FA0D" box="[372,444,1418,1444]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7B164A7992FA482557FA0D" box="[455,525,1418,1444]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Bahia</collectingRegion>
: “Rio Belmonte [Rio Jequitinhonha]”, 1816, 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A7C59FA4923D5FA0C" box="[1036,1167,1419,1445]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Anonymous</emphasis>
[Wied] 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A7CB9FA492249FA0D" box="[1260,1299,1419,1444]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">s.n.</emphasis>
(TO! [digital image]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7B164A78E8FA1025AEF9D5" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7B164A78E8FA1025AEF9D5" blockId="11.[136,1452,1382,1984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A78E8FA1026D7FA45" bold="true" box="[189,397,1490,1516]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7B164A79FFFA10256CFA45" author="Colla, L. A." box="[426,566,1490,1516]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" refId="ref18398" refString="Colla, L. A. (1833) Herbarium Pedemontanum, Vol. 1. Augustae Taurinorum: Ex Typis Regiis, Torino, 566 pp." type="book" year="1833">Colla (1833)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7B164A7A3CFA102453FA44" author="Fryxell, P. A." box="[617,777,1490,1517]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" pagination="589 - 593" refId="ref18668" refString="Fryxell, P. A. (1976) On some Brazilian Malvaceae of Martius, published by Colla in 1833. Taxon 25: 589 - 593. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1220115" type="journal article" year="1976">Fryxell (1976)</bibRefCitation>
attributed the 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B7B164A7BF3FA11248CFA44" box="[934,982,1491,1517]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">type</typeStatus>
collection to Martius, who never collected at Rio Jequitinhonha. Wied collected over 100 species at “Rio Belmonte” (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7B164A7B94FA3423CDF9B9" author="Moraes, P. L. R. &amp; De Smedt, S. &amp; Esser, H. J. &amp; Gallagher, C. &amp; Guglielmone, L." box="[961,1175,1526,1552]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" pagination="23 - 36" refId="ref20049" refString="Moraes, P. L. R., De Smedt, S., Esser, H. J., Gallagher, C. &amp; Guglielmone, L. (2013) On some Brazilian plants distributed by Martius in 1827 and published by Colla in 1833. Harvard Papers in Botany 18: 23 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.3100 / 025.018.0105" type="journal article" year="2013">
Moraes 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A7C48FA35230EF9B9" box="[1053,1108,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7B164A7CFDFA342205F9B9" authorityName="Martius ex Colla" authorityYear="1833" box="[1192,1375,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nemorensis">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A7CFDFA342205F9B9" box="[1192,1375,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Sida nemorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species of section 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A7A32F9D82585F99D" box="[615,735,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Nelavagae</emphasis>
by the aristate mericarps, by the presence of glandular trichomes in the stems, and by the erect habit (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7B164A7A75F9FC259FF9F1" box="[544,709,1598,1624]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="13.[136,229,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,190,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[190,1398,190,1896]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 6. A–D. Sida nemorensis. A. Flower. B. Branch with leaves and flowers. C. Leaves and schizocarps. D. Calyx and mericarps. E–J. Sida paradoxa. E. Flower. F. Branch with leaves and stipules. G. Abaxial surface of leaf. H. Habit. I–J. Schizocarps. K–P. Sida planicaulis. K. Flowers. L. Adaxial surface of leaf. M. Abaxial surface of leaf. N. Branch with distichous leaves arrangement. O. Schizocarps. P. Branch with flowers and schizocarps. PhotographsA–B by Amaury Junior, C–P by Martin Grings (C–D from Krapovickas &amp; Cristóbal 38480, HAS)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415499/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Figures 6A–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7B164A7A85F9FC25A0F9F1" box="[720,762,1598,1624]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">14J</figureCitation>
; 
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B7B164A7B53F9FC240DF9F1" box="[774,855,1598,1624]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7B164A7B27F9FC231CF9F0" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[882,1094,1598,1625]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" pagination="5 - 45" refId="ref19451" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2006) Las especies argentinas y de paises vecinos de Sida secc. Nelavaga (Malvaceae, Malveae). Bonplandia 15: 5 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 151 - 289" type="journal article" year="2006">Krapovickas 2006</bibRefCitation>
). In the present work, photos of the species in its habitat are presented for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7B164A78E8F944234CF8FD" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7B164A78E8F944234CF8FD" blockId="11.[136,1452,1382,1984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A78E8F94425BFF909" bold="true" box="[189,741,1670,1696]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7B164A7B54F94424E0F909" authorityName="Martius ex Colla" authorityYear="1833" box="[769,954,1670,1696]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nemorensis">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A7B54F94424E0F909" box="[769,954,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Sida nemorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7B164A7C61F94423D3F909" box="[1076,1161,1670,1696]" name="Bolivia" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7B164A7CC3F94523A5F908" box="[1174,1279,1671,1697]" name="Paraguay" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7B164A7D5EF9442220F909" box="[1291,1402,1670,1696]" name="Argentina" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and southeast, midwest and south of 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7B164A79AEF9682565F96D" box="[507,575,1706,1732]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7B164A7A1AF968247BF96D" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[591,801,1706,1732]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" pagination="5 - 45" refId="ref19451" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2006) Las especies argentinas y de paises vecinos de Sida secc. Nelavaga (Malvaceae, Malveae). Bonplandia 15: 5 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 151 - 289" type="journal article" year="2006">Krapovickas 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7B164A7B7BF96824E5F96D" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[814,959,1706,1732]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In state of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7B164A7C18F968227EF96D" box="[1101,1316,1706,1732]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, the species was found so far only in two places, in Coastal grassland associated with 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7B164A7BE3F90D27E1F8A4" authority="Noblick &amp; Lorenzi (2010: 164)" authorityName="Noblick &amp; Lorenzi" authorityPageNumber="164" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Butia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="catarinensis">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A7BE3F90D23D8F941" box="[950,1154,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Butia catarinensis</emphasis>
Noblick &amp; Lorenzi (2010: 164)
</taxonomicName>
and in Inland subtropical Forest (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7B164A7A63F93025C2F8A4" box="[566,664,1778,1805]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="12.[136,229,2030,2052]" captionTargetBox="[315,1294,482,1962]" captionTargetId="figure-118@12.[258,1329,425,2006]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution map of Sida glaziovii, S. paradoxa, S. linifolia, S. nemorensis, S. planicaulis, S. potentilloides and S. rubifolia in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415497/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Figure 5</figureCitation>
), in edges. With the available records, the species presents an EOO of 2,734,283.060 Km² and an AOO of 170 Km². Although it can be considered EN by the AOO, conditions B(a), B(b) and B(c) were not met. Therefore, the species is here considered Least Concern (LC).
</paragraph>
